<p>I know there are many other questions on SO regarding the error "Given URL is not allowed by the Application configuration" but I have done ALL of those recommendations and nothing works, I hope I am missing something.  I am using the Angular Module ngFacebook to accomplish Facebook login </p>  <p><a href="https://github.com/GoDisco/ngFacebook" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/GoDisco/ngFacebook</a></p>  <p>Here is my app module:</p>  <pre><code>angular.module('yakkerHub', ["yakkerHub.Routes", "yakkerHub.Controllers", "ngFacebook"]) .config( function( $facebookProvider ) {      $facebookProvider.setAppId('#########'); })     .run( function( $rootScope) {           // Load the facebook SDK asynchronously         (function () {             // If we've already installed the SDK, we're done             if (document.getElementById('facebook-jssdk')) {                 return;             }              // Get the first script element, which we'll use to find the parent node             var firstScriptElement = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];              // Create a new script element and set its id             var facebookJS = document.createElement('script');             facebookJS.id = 'facebook-jssdk';              // Set the new script's source to the source of the Facebook JS SDK             facebookJS.src = '//connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js';              // Insert the Facebook JS SDK into the DOM             firstScriptElement.parentNode.insertBefore(facebookJS, firstScriptElement);         }());     }); </code></pre>  <p>My Facebook App ID has been omited on purpose and I have double checked that this App ID matches what is the Facebook Developer portal.</p>  <p>I have a login Controller like this that if the login is successful will switch to the "/yaksomething" route</p>  <pre><code>controllerModule.controller('loginCtrl', function($scope, $location, $routeParams, $facebook) {  $scope.destination = $routeParams["towhere"];   $scope.login = function() {     $facebook.login().then(function() {         refresh();     }); };  function refresh() {     $facebook.api("/me").then(         function(response) {             //$scope.welcomeMsg = "Welcome " + response.name;             $scope.userParams.loggedin = true;             $scope.userParams.userID = response.id;             $scope.userParams.userName = response.name;               $location.path("/yaksomething");         },         function(err) {             $scope.welcomeMsg = "Please log in";         }); };    //refresh();    }); </code></pre>  <p>Here are my settings in the Facebook Developer Portal for this App</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/ObBg8.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/ObBg8.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Here are the Advanced OAuth settings</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/flzRu.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/flzRu.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I have of course added the Web platform.  From everything I see this all works correct but I get the "Given URL is not allowed by the Application configuration" every time the login function is executed in the loginCtrl.  I am out of ideas, please help....  </p>